#ROOMS
#64100
Name Before the Palace~
Desc To the north the majestic stone gates to the palace lay open. More symbolic 
than utilitarian, the sheer mass of the gates would easily take a small army 
of men to close much less open. To the south, a miniature replica of the 
palace gates opens to the temple of Graal. To the east and west of this 
cobbled area the districts of metal and silk meet the district of flames. 
~
Sector city~
Exit east 64101
Exit west 64111
End


#64101
Name A District Intersection~
Desc Cobblestones continue unabated in multiple directions from here. To the west 
of this intersection the southern entrance to the Palace is visible and the 
area here is visibly muted for it. To the north, gardens and stalls of 
flowers dominate the path. To the south, the faint sound of hymns being sung 
echoes through the area. 
~
Sector city~
Exit north 64154
Exit south 64152
Exit west 64100
Exit southeast 64102
End


#64102
Name Along the District of Flames~
